OL,3,CWhy politicians are voting over
OL,4,Cwhether to suspend a former Chief
OL,5,CMinister
OL,7,FGuernsey's politicians are debating
OL,8,Fwhether to suspend a former Chief
OL,9,FMinister.
OL,11,FDeputy Gavin St Pier, the current Vice-
OL,12,FPresident for Policy & Resources, was
OL,13,Ffound to have broken the States' Code
OL,14,Fof Conduct by talking to a national
OL,15,Fnewspaper reporter about a local
OL,16,Fdoctor.
OL,18,FThe States of Guernsey began debating
OL,19,Fthe motion today (Wednesday 26
OL,20,FOctober), with a vote to follow.
