OL,3,CWhy politicians are voting over
OL,4,Cwhether to suspend a former Chief
OL,5,CMinister
OL,7,FSome families have defended Deputy St
OL,8,FPier, with a letter from 17
OL,9,Fsignatories arguing that the
OL,10,Fsuspension would set a dangerous
OL,11,Fprecedent.
OL,13,FWhat are the States voting on?
OL,15,FStates members will vote on whether
OL,16,FDeputy Gavin St Pier should be
OL,17,Fsuspended from the States for 25 days.
OL,19,FThey are asked to consider the
OL,20,Ffindings of a report published in July
OL,21,Fregarding Dr Sandie Bohin's complaint.
